article.story: CONWAY, S.C. -- — Izaiyah Nelson had 16 points in Arkansas State's 71-60 win against Coastal Carolina on Wednesday night. Nelson added 12 rebounds for the Red Wolves (16-14, 11-6 Sun Belt Conference). Dyondre Dominguez scored 14 points and added seven rebounds. Derrian Ford was 3 of 10 shooting (1 for 6 from 3-point range) to finish with nine points, while adding eight rebounds. The Red Wolves picked up their sixth straight victory. Jacob Meyer finished with 17 points for the Chanticleers (8-20, 5-12). John Ojiako added 14 points and 15 rebounds for Coastal Carolina. In addition, Kevin Easley Jr. had 12 points. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
